cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the task of 3D face reconstruction, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also uses 3D Morphable Model (3DMM), which is a technique used in computer graphics and geometric modeling, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the accuracy of the reconstruction, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm to solve the problem of face reconstruction under large pose, which involves a combination of geometric and machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves experimental evaluation of the proposed algorithm, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
